1. Launch AWS and Login
2. Create EC2 Instance - LinuxVM
3. Connect to LinuxVM EC2
- Go to folder where .pem file is present
- run ssh -i <.pemfile> <ec2-user@PublicIP>
4. Change password auth to yes
- switch to root user --> sudo su -
-run vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config
-click i for Inser
-change passwordAuthentication to yes
-press Esc
-type :wq then enter
4. Create EC2 user password - ec2-user
- run passwd ec2-user
